sdlconsole
------------------------------------------
SDL_Console is a drop down console that can be easily added to any SDL
application. It is similar to Quake and other games consoles. A console gives
you the ability to interact with your program in an easy way by executing
predefined commands. You can also have more than one console at a time.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.0.4-1
  libSDL1.2_0-1.2.15-3
  libSDL_console-devel-2.1-1bl1
  libSDL_console2.1_0-2.1-1bl1
  libSDL_image1.2_0-1.2.12-5

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-2
  cygport-0.20.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.3-1
  libtool-2.4.6-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://wacha.ch/wiki/sdlconsole/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/sdlconsole/sdlconsole-2.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack sdlconsole-2.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./sdlconsole-2.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/sdlconsole-2.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/sdlconsole-2.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libSDL_console2.1_0-2.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libSDL_console-devel-2.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(sdlconsole)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/sdlconsole.README
  /usr/share/doc/sdlconsole/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/sdlconsole/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/sdlconsole/README

(libSDL_console2.1_0)
  /usr/bin/cygSDL_console-2-1-0.dll

(libSDL_console-devel)
  /usr/include/SDL_console/DT_drawtext.h
  /usr/include/SDL_console/SDL_console.h
  /usr/include/SDL_console/internal.h
  /usr/lib/libSDL_console.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/sdl_console.pc

